        {
          "username": "Meeka G Select",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "110694909547346912420",
          "user_review_count": 48,
          "user_photo_count": 1,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtafUMxGHW0qjO5i4WtxjHpo0zYC-nVStbnwMNDoGWj4Cy7KU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I recently visited the Emergency Room at NYC Health + Hospitals/Metropolitan on 1st Avenue, and overall, my experience was better than I expected given how busy emergency departments in New York City usually are.\n\nThe ER was active when I arrived, but the triage staff worked efficiently to assess patients and prioritize care. The nurses were professional and direct, yet still compassionate. Even during a hectic shift, they made an effort to explain what was happening and what the next steps would be, which helped reduce a lot of the anxiety that naturally comes with an emergency visit.\n\nThe medical team was thorough during my evaluation. The doctor took time to ask detailed questions and didn\u2019t rush through the examination. I appreciated that they explained test results clearly and provided practical discharge instructions. It felt organized despite the high patient volume.\n\nThe facility itself is not luxurious, but it is functional and clean. Seating can be limited during peak hours, so wait times may vary depending on how critical other cases are. That\u2019s typical for a city hospital serving a large community.\n\nWhat stood out most to me was the dedication of the staff. Emergency rooms are high-pressure environments, and the team handled it with professionalism and care. For anyone in the East Harlem area needing urgent medical attention, Metropolitan\u2019s ER provides dependable service with a strong focus on patient care.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xoQ1JsQjZhV2R6WW5WWmVUTTJWVVJrVWw4MVFsRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x109f241bdc20e3a!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOlhCRlB6aWdzYnVZeTM2VURkUl81QlE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "3 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-03-13T23:28:30+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Isaias Guzman",
          "rating": 3,
          "contributor_id": "114563814022588399647",
          "user_review_count": 1,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU19SXSPog4MLX4s9X020sbgr_ig3w0icMN2LgB34KzQT0S0JoJ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I went in with my mother and was translating for her. The staff member in the afternoon who was intake/registration was very disrespectful. I usually don\u2019t write reviews, but I felt it was important to share this experience.\nWhen I informed him that my mother did not have insurance, he responded by saying, \u201cjust so you know, this is a city hospital, it  doent mean is  free.\u201d I clearly understood that and acknowledged it. The entire conversation was in Spanish.\nHowever, he then made side comments about our situation, assuming I did not understand what he was saying. I felt very disrespected and uncomfortable. I did respond and made it clear that I never said the service was free, nor made any such comments. I felt judged and discriminated against because of my mother\u2019s lack of insurance.\nDespite this experience, I am giving 3 stars because everyone else was amazing. Thank you to the nurse who took the vitals, the nurse who performed the blood tests, and all the other staff involved. Most importantly, thank you to the physician. As a young person, you showed compassion and saw the human side of my situation and my mother\u2019s, and you truly tried to help us.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pkSlUxVnpkMUp6WDNaRk5ITnlhR05yYm0xNE0zYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x109f241bdc20e3a!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOjdJU1Vzd1JzX3ZFNHNyaGNrbm14M3c%7C%7C?hl=en",
